segment.source: Searching for Fixed Applications in Compatibility Administrator (Windows 10)
segment.target: Searching for Fixed Applications in Compatibility Administrator (Windows 10)

segment.source: With the search functionality in Compatibility Administrator, you can locate specific executable (.exe) files with previously applied compatibility fixes, compatibility modes, or AppHelp messages.
segment.target: With the search functionality in Compatibility Administrator, you can locate specific executable (.exe) files with previously applied compatibility fixes, compatibility modes, or AppHelp messages.

segment.source: With the search functionality in Compatibility Administrator, you can locate specific executable (.exe) files with previously applied compatibility fixes, compatibility modes, or AppHelp messages.
segment.target: With the search functionality in Compatibility Administrator, you can locate specific executable (.exe) files with previously applied compatibility fixes, compatibility modes, or AppHelp messages.

segment.source: This is particularly useful if you are trying to identify applications with a specific compatibility fix or identifying which fixes are applied to a specific application.
segment.target: This is particularly useful if you are trying to identify applications with a specific compatibility fix or identifying which fixes are applied to a specific application.

segment.source: The Query Compatibility Databases tool provides additional search options.
segment.target: The Query Compatibility Databases tool provides additional search options.

segment.source: For more information, see Searching for Installed Compatibility Fixes with the Query Tool in Compatibility Administrator.
segment.target: For more information, see Searching for Installed Compatibility Fixes with the Query Tool in Compatibility Administrator.

segment.source: Searching for Previously Applied Compatibility Fixes
segment.target: Searching for Previously Applied Compatibility Fixes

segment.source: Important
segment.target: Important

segment.source: You must perform your search with the correct version of the Compatibility Administrator tool.
segment.target: You must perform your search with the correct version of the Compatibility Administrator tool.

segment.source: If you are searching for a 32-bit custom database, you must use the 32-bit version of Compatibility Administrator.
segment.target: If you are searching for a 32-bit custom database, you must use the 32-bit version of Compatibility Administrator.

segment.source: If you are searching for a 64-bit custom database, you must use the 64-bit version of Compatibility Administrator.
segment.target: If you are searching for a 64-bit custom database, you must use the 64-bit version of Compatibility Administrator.

segment.source: To search for previous fixes
segment.target: To search for previous fixes

segment.source: On the Compatibility Administrator toolbar, click Search.
segment.target: On the Compatibility Administrator toolbar, click Search.

segment.source: Click Browse to locate the directory location to search for .exe files.
segment.target: Click Browse to locate the directory location to search for .exe files.

segment.source: Select at least one check box from Entries with Compatibility Fixes, Entries with Compatibility Modes, or Entries with AppHelp.
segment.target: Select at least one check box from Entries with Compatibility Fixes, Entries with Compatibility Modes, or Entries with AppHelp.

segment.source: Click Find Now.
segment.target: Click Find Now.

segment.source: The query runs, returning your results in the lower pane.
segment.target: The query runs, returning your results in the lower pane.

segment.source: Viewing Your Query Results
segment.target: Viewing Your Query Results

segment.source: Your query results display the affected files, the application location, the application name, the type of compatibility fix, and the custom database that provided the fix.
segment.target: Your query results display the affected files, the application location, the application name, the type of compatibility fix, and the custom database that provided the fix.

segment.source: Exporting Your Query Results
segment.target: Exporting Your Query Results

segment.source: You can export your search results to a text (.txt) file for later review or archival.
segment.target: You can export your search results to a text (.txt) file for later review or archival.

segment.source: To export your search results
segment.target: To export your search results

segment.source: In the Search for Fixes dialog box, click Export.
segment.target: In the Search for Fixes dialog box, click Export.

segment.source: Browse to the location where you want to store your search result file, and then click Save.
segment.target: Browse to the location where you want to store your search result file, and then click Save.
